dvanced technical skills\" background_color_front=\"#10086d\" title_front_color=\"#ffffff\" text_front_color=\"#ffffff\" background_color_back=\"#fb660c\" title_back_color=\"#ffffff\" text_back_color=\"#ffffff\" border_size=\"1px\" border_color=\"\" border_radius=\"4px\" icon=\"fa-user-md\" icon_color=\"#fb660c\" circle=\"yes\" circle_color=\"#ffffff\" circle_border_color=\"#ffffff\" icon_rotate=\"\" icon_spin=\"no\" image=\"\" image_width=\"35\" image_height=\"35\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\"]We have the safest anesthesia equipment in the industry. All surgical patients receive continuous readings of ECG, blood pressure, pulse oximetry, respiration and temperature monitoring.\r\n\r\n[button link=\"/regionalvet/specialty-services/surgery/\" color=\"blue\" size=\"large\" stretch=\"\" type=\"\" shape=\"\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\" gradient_colors=\"|\" gradient_hover_colors=\"|\" accent_color=\"\" accent_hover_color=\"\" bevel_color=\"\" border_width=\"1px\" icon=\"fa-medkit\" icon_divider=\"yes\" icon_position=\"right\" modal=\"\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\" alignment=\"center\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]More on Surgery[/button][/flip_box][flip_box title_front=\"Cardiology\" title_back=\"Focuses on diseases that affect the heart and lungs\" text_front=\"Congenital, valvular, pericardial, and myocardial (muscular) cardiac diseases are common among our pets and often go undetected until the disease is in advanced stages.\" background_color_front=\"#10086d\" title_front_color=\"#ffffff\" text_front_color=\"#ffffff\" background_color_back=\"#fb660c\" title_back_color=\"#ffffff\" text_back_color=\"#ffffff\" border_size=\"1px\" border_color=\"\" border_radius=\"4px\" icon=\"fa-heart\" icon_color=\"#fb660c\" circle=\"yes\" circle_color=\"#ffffff\" circle_border_color=\"#ffffff\" icon_rotate=\"\" icon_spin=\"no\" image=\"\" image_width=\"35\" image_height=\"35\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\"]For more complex cardiovascular disease, advanced color flow Doppler, vascular contrast studies, nuclear cardiovascular medicine, and Holter Monitoring may be needed. RegionalVet performs each of those.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"/regionalvet/specialty-services/cardiology/\" color=\"blue\" size=\"large\" stretch=\"\" type=\"\" shape=\"\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\" gradient_colors=\"|\" gradient_hover_colors=\"|\" accent_color=\"\" accent_hover_color=\"\" bevel_color=\"\" border_width=\"1px\" icon=\"fa-medkit\" icon_divider=\"yes\" icon_position=\"right\" modal=\"\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\" alignment=\"center\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]More on Cardiology[/button]</p>[/flip_box][flip_box title_front=\"Internal Medicine\" title_back=\"Diagnosis and (nonsurgical) treatment of diseased internal organs.\" text_front=\"Veterinary Internists are sought for the most baffling cases.\" background_color_front=\"#10086d\" title_front_color=\"#ffffff\" text_front_color=\"#ffffff\" background_color_back=\"#fb660c\" title_back_color=\"#ffffff\" text_back_color=\"#ffffff\" border_size=\"1px\" border_color=\"\" border_radius=\"4px\" icon=\"fa-plus-circle\" icon_color=\"#fb660c\" circle=\"yes\" circle_color=\"#ffffff\" circle_border_color=\"#ffffff\" icon_rotate=\"\" icon_spin=\"no\" image=\"\" image_width=\"35\" image_height=\"35\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"1\" animation_offset=\"\"]Examples of the problems handled by our Internists:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Gastrointestinal Diseases</li>\r\n 	<li>Endocrine Disorders</li>\r\n 	<li>Immune Disorders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"/regionalvet/specialty-services/internal-medicine/\" color=\"blue\" size=\"large\" stretch=\"\" type=\"\" shape=\"\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\" gradient_colors=\"|\" gradient_hover_colors=\"|\" accent_color=\"\" accent_hover_color=\"\" bevel_color=\"\" border_width=\"1px\" icon=\"fa-medkit\" icon_divider=\"yes\" icon_position=\"right\" modal=\"\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\" alignment=\"center\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]More on Internal Medicine[/button]</p>[/flip_box][/flip_boxes][separator style_type=\"none\" top_margin=\"30\" bottom_margin=\"\" sep_color=\"\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"\" alignment=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][one_full last=\"yes\" spacing=\"yes\" center_content=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"center center\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" border_position=\"all\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"solid\" padding=\"\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" animation_type=\"0\" animation_direction=\"down\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][title size=\"2\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"double solid\" sep_color=\"#10086d\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff6319;\">One Hospital, Many Solutions</span></h2>\r\n[/title][fusion_text]RegionalVet is an integrated hospital that offers many specialties and methods of care. As such, we partner with many surrounding veterinarians to assist in ways there practice may not be able to. There are multiple options when helping you\'re pet, we can help you find the right one.[/fusion_text][separator style_type=\"none\" top_margin=\"30\" bottom_margin=\"\" sep_color=\"\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"\" alignment=\"center\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][/one_full][one_full last=\"yes\" spacing=\"yes\" center_content=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"left top\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" border_position=\"all\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"\" padding=\"\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" animation_type=\"\" animation_direction=\"\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" animation_offset=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][fusion_tabs design=\"classic\" layout=\"horizontal\" justified=\"no\" backgroundcolor=\"#ffffff\" inactivecolor=\"\" bordercolor=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][fusion_tab title=\"Dermatology\" icon=\"fa-tint\"]The dermatology team at RegionalVet specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of dogs and cats with disorders of the skin, ears, hair, and nails. We know how frustrating these conditions can be for you and your treasured companion. Our skin experts aim to restore comfort and well-being using the latest techniques and highest standard of care.\r\n\r\nSkin conditions often require long-term monitoring to keep flare-ups at bay. Together with your primary veterinarian the dermatology team at RegionalVet will effectively implement a treatment protocol tailored for your pet.\r\n\r\nWhile RegionalVet does not currently have a Dermatologist in the office, we are completing refills for existing dermatology patients.\r\n\r\nBe sure to ask your primary veterinarian about the Dermatology Service at RegionalVet. Here are some of the conditions we treat:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bacterial skin infections (pyoderma)</li>\r\n 	<li>Yeast/fungal skin infections</li>\r\n 	<li>Food allergies</li>\r\n 	<li>Flea allergy dermatitis</li>\r\n 	<li>Environmental allergies (atopic dermatitis)</li>\r\n 	<li>Ectoparasitic diseases (fleas, ticks, mites and lice)</li>\r\n 	<li>Pododermatitis (disease of the foot)</li>\r\n 	<li>Auto-immune skin disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Endocrine/metabolic skin disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Drug reactions</li>\r\n 	<li>Chronic ear disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Skin cancer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us for a consultation at 856.728.1400</strong>[/fusion_tab][fusion_tab title=\"Radiology\" icon=\"fa-bullseye\"]The sooner a condition is diagnosed, the sooner healing can begin. Ultrasoundand Digital X-rays are some of the methods used by our doctors to find out what the best course of treatment is for your companion. With our leading-edge technology we can view crystal clear images on our flat-panel monitors anywhere in the hospital. We can enlarge scans and view different angles with the simple click of a mouse.\r\n\r\nOur attending doctors review every x-ray taken at RegionalVet, provide you right away with a preliminary reading and then submit the x-rays to a Board Certified Radiologist. All findings are then forwarded to your primary veterinarian. We will personally call you within 48 hours if there are changes to your pet\'s treatment plan as a result of the second review.\r\n\r\nResearch shows that abnormalities are missed in 30% of cases on radiographs (x-rays) seen by only one doctor. Your primary veterinarian may already be consulting with our radiology team to help review images taken at his or her facility.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Abdominal, Thoracic and Soft Tissue Ultrasound</li>\r\n 	<li>GI &amp; Vascular Contrast Studies</li>\r\n 	<li>Ultrasound Guided Biopsies and Aspirates</li>\r\n 	<li>X-ray Interpretation and Consults</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDiagnostic Imaging at RegionalVet is a vital resource for pet parents and veterinarians throughout South Jersey.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us for a consultation today 888.830.8844.</strong>\r\n<pre></pre>\r\n[/fusion_tab][fusion_tab title=\"Surgery\" icon=\"fa-user-md\"]Whether your pet requires a minimally invasive procedure or the most complicated life-saving intervention, the surgical team at RegionalVet can accommodate the needs of your companion. With our commitment to a standard of excellence you can expect integrity and compassion from our highly skilled surgical team lead by board certified specialists. All of our surgeons possess extensive surgical knowledge, superb clinical judgment, and advanced technical skills acquired over many years of education and experience.\r\n\r\nEach of our state-of-the-art, sterile surgical suites are comparable to the operating rooms in a human hospital. We have the safest anesthesia equipment in the industry. All surgical patients receive continuous readings of ECG, blood pressure, pulse oximetry, respiration and temperature monitoring during and after the anesthetic experience. In addition, endoscopy can be used before and during surgery to allow our doctors to visualize internal portions of your pet\'s body without making additional incisions. This can assist in both determining diagnoses, as well as ensuring your pet\'s procedure is as minimally invasive as possible.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us for a consultation at 888.830.8844.</strong>[/fusion_tab][fusion_tab title=\"Cardiology\" icon=\"fa-heart\"]Veterinary cardiology, just like human cardiology, is a specialty in medicine that focuses on diseases that affect the heart and lungs. Congenital, valvular, pericardial, and myocardial (muscular) cardiac diseases are common among our pets and often go undetected until the disease is in advanced stages. Early and appropriate diagnosis and treatment of heart disease is essential for the best prognosis and quality of life for your pet.\r\n\r\nThe Cardiology Team at RegionalVetis trained to perform advanced non-invasive and minimally invasive diagnostics to evaluate your pet for underlying cardiovascular disease. Many cardiac diseases can be diagnosed with a simple non-invasive echocardiogram which uses ultrasound to view the structure and function of the heart.\r\n\r\nHowever, for more complex cardiovascular disease, advanced color flow Doppler, vascular contrast studies, nuclear cardiovascular medicine, and Holter Monitoring may be needed. RegionalVet performs each of those.[/fusion_tab][fusion_tab title=\"Internal Medicine\" icon=\"fa-plus-circle\"]\r\n<h3 class=\"flip-box-heading-back\">A SPECIALIZATION WHICH DEALS WITH THE DIAGNOSIS AND (NONSURGICAL) TREATMENT OF DISEASED INTERNAL ORGANS THAT AFFECT YOUR PET\'S BODY AS A WHOLE.</h3>\r\nExamples of the problems handled by our Internists:\r\n\r\n<strong>Gastrointestinal Diseases</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Chronic Vomiting &amp;Diarrhea</li>\r\n 	<li>Endoscopic Diagnosis</li>\r\n 	<li>Liver and Kidney Disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Acute &amp; Chronic Hepatitis</li>\r\n 	<li>Acute &amp; Chronic KidneyFailure</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Endocrine Disorders</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Difficult Diabetes</li>\r\n 	<li>Cushings Disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Airway Disease</li>\r\n 	<li>Feline Asthma</li>\r\n 	<li>Chronic Cough</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Immune Disorders</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>IMHA (Immune Mediated Hemolytic Anemia)</li>\r\n 	<li>ITP (Immune Mediated Thrombocytopenia)</li>\r\n 	<li>Polyarthritis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/fusion_tab][/fusion_tabs][/one_full][button link=\"/contact-us\" color=\"blue\" size=\"xlarge\"  stretch=\"no\"  type=\"flat\" shape=\"square\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\" gradient_colors=\"|\" gradient_hover_colors=\"#10086d|\" accent_color=\"\" accent_hover_color=\"\" bevel_color=\"\" border_width=\"\" icon=\"fa-check-circle-o\" icon_position=\"left\" icon_divider=\"yes\" modal=\"\" animation_type=\"slide\" animation_direction=\"left\" animation_speed=\"1\" animation_offset=\"\" alignment=\"center\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Contact Us Now![/button]'),(20758,72,'fusion_builder_converted','yes'),(20759,69,'fusion_builder_content_backup','[one_half last=\"no\" spacing=\"yes\" center_content=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"left top\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"\" padding=\"\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" animation_type=\"\" animation_direction=\"\" animation_speed=\"0.1\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][slider width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][slide type=\"image\" link=\"\" linktarget=\"\" lightbox=\"\"]http://dev.advertisingb